        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1544",
        "content": "It does not take much of this sort of thing to wreck an ordinary friendship, so before long Rebecca and Emma Jane sat in one end of the railway train in going to and from Riverboro, and Huldah occupied the other with her court.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-high_s-normal_e-normal",
