        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-1544",
        "content": "Miss Maxwell, as the niece of one of Maine's ex governors and the daughter of one of Bowdoin's professors, was the most remarkable personality in Wareham, and that her few years of teaching happened to be in Rebecca's time was the happiest of all chances.",
        "style_prompt": "F_p-high_s-fast_e-low",
